{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"1. Create HTML Page","anchor":"1-Create-HTML-Page"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Every website have few pages associated with it, lets see how to make a HTMLPage using HTMLKit","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["   struct FirstPage: HTMLPage {","","        \/\/\/ Your HTMLContent","        var htmlContent: [HTMLBlock] {","","          Heading(.h1, \"Random Image\")","","          Image(src: \"https:\/\/picsum.photos\/200\/300\", alt: \"Test\")","   ","          HorizontalRule()","       }","    }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a struct and implement the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/HTMLSwiftKit\/documentation\/HTMLSwiftKit\/HTMLPage","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol, and you are good to start building your page."}]},{"text":"2. Create CSS","anchor":"2-Create-CSS","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now just like every normal HTML page you need to give some CSS to it, so HTMLSwiftKit covers that too."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["   struct BasicCSS: CSSBlock {","   ","     var cssType: CSSType = .custom","   ","     var content: [CSSModifier] {","         Border(5, border: .dotted, color: \"orange\")","         BackgroundColor(color: \"yellow\")","         FontSize(22)","         Color(\"Red\")","         Padding(200)","     }","   }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a struct implement the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/HTMLSwiftKit\/documentation\/HTMLSwiftKit\/CSSBlock","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol and provide the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" and start adding your styling modifiers.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Make sure you add your CSS block into your HTMLContent block to allow HTML to get context of it"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"code":[" var htmlContent: [HTMLBlock] {","        Style({ BasicCSS() })"," }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"3-Configure-Website","text":"3. Configure Website"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Once the HTMLPages and CSS are ready, now its tme to configure your website","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":[" struct MyWebSite: WebSite {"," ","     var baseUrl: URL = URL(string: \"www.htmlswiftkit.com\")!"," ","     var author: String = \"Gokul\""," ","     var pages: [HTMLSwiftKit.HTMLPage] = [FirstPage(), SecondPage()]"," ","     var crawlerConfiguration: CrawlerConfiguration = CrawlerConfig()"," }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a struct implement the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"website"},{"text":" protocol and provide the necessary data and you have configured your website.","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"text":"4. Generate\/Publish","anchor":"4-GeneratePublish","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once you are ready with your Website configuration now its time to generate the Site source code."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"So HTMLSwiftKit provides two way to generate your source code:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"1-Using-SPM","text":"1. Using SPM"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To generate the site via SPM, create your own new SPM, add HTMLSwiftKit as a dependency and configure the above mentioned things. Once you have done all the stpes mentioned create an instance of the website and trigger the "},{"code":"publishViaSPM()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" method"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@main","struct StartWebsite {","    static func main() {","        let site = MyWebSite()","        ","        do {","            try site.publishViaSPM()","        } catch {","            print(error.localizedDescription)","        }","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On generating Site via SPM, the kit creates a Build folder into your existing package."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Check this starter project to understand more.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"2-Using-iOS-Device","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"2. Using iOS Device"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To generate the site via Device, create a new project and add HTMLSwiftKit as a dependency and configure the above mentioned things. Once you have done all the stpes mentioned create an instance of the website and trigger the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"publishViaDevice()"},{"text":" method","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@main","struct StartWebsite {","    static func main() {","        let site = MyWebSite()","        ","        do {","            try site.publishViaDevice()","        } catch {","            print(error.localizedDescription)","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Check this starter project to understand more.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"By following the given procedure you can build your static site easily.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/HTMLSwiftKit\/documentation\/HTMLSwiftKit\/GettingStarted","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/htmlswiftkit\/gettingstarted"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/HTMLSwiftKit\/documentation\/HTMLSwiftKit"]]},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"HTMLSwiftKit"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"Getting Started"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text"